<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99711891720657></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99711891720657><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99711891720657>Soloing a shaman lvl 1 to 51</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99711891720657#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 6th 1:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To solo, the most inportant things is to kill the mob before the mob kills you.&nbsp;&nbsp;In other words how much damage you do in x amount of time is what counts.  The damage potenctul of a shaman changes as he/she goes up in lvl.  Lvl 1-13, most damage is done by your weapon.  Lvl 14-33 damage by spell becomes more and more inportant.  Lvl 34+ spell damage continues to play a larger roll, and pet damage becomes more and more inportant.  <br>Soloing lvl 1-13<br>You need to asap get the spell burst of flam.  Then cast this dd from a safe location on passing mobs. Melee the mob to death.  Note Slow spells can be used on mobs with fast attack speed like lepords.  You should alway buff the following when ever meleeing. Str, dex, and agi.  Ac buff also can make a real differance.<br>Soloing lvl 14-23<br>at lvl 14 you get your first big dd spell, and your dot spell begin to do good damage. During these lvl root and nuke or nuke kiting are common.  You should however continue to melee for at least part of the kill.  This will keep your melee skill up, which is inportant at higher lvl.  Lots of people say that after lvl such and such a shaman can't do meaningful damage with their weapon.  With the right weapon (a high damage 2hb) your weapon can do as much damage over time as your pet or as your best dot until lvl 49.  <br><br>Lvl 24-33 Soloing<br>at lvl 24 you get some great buffs that alow you to melee mobs again.  Pull the mob with slow and dot it.  Be sure to buff yourself with speed before each fight.  You should always buff the following Speed, regen, str, dex and agi.  At higher lvl sta is also a good buff.  <br><br>Lvl 34+ Soloing<br>Some put down the shaman pet, probalbly because they don't understand the intended relation of pet to shaman.  Unlike other pet classes shaman have good melee skills and should thus have the mob attacking them while the pet attacks the mob. Again pull with slow, sick the pet on the mob. (pet should be buffed with speed and str and dex). Cast sickness based dot on mob.  Note the pet should be able to stop the mobs charge or taunt it off you.  Casting the sickness based dot should not pull the mob off the pet. Cast poision based dot.  This dot will pull most mobs off the pet.  You and the pet melee the mob while the dots work.  Note for some mobs you will need to recast the poision dot.  Also if the second poision dot or the sickness dot come off you need to recast slow before it comes off.  <br>This type of soloing ueses all the important abilites of shaman, melee, dot, slow, regen, buffing and pet.  <br>In this type of soloing AC and a high damage weapon are as inportant as high wis.  <br>Here are some of the zones and mobs I soloed.  Note some of this was before kunark, you might say i don't play as much as some....<br><br>I stayed in EF until lvl 14<br>EF is typical of the type of zones you want to look for to solo in.  Lots of wondering mobs around but with safe spots to pull to.  <br>After this I think I did the gnolls in EK, and gnolls in HH, and the birds in SK.  <br>After lvl 24 I started doing the totemic quest and moved around alot.  At lvl 34 I went to FM zone and hunted at the giant fort.  I then moved to the Yeti caves in DL and then to the gaint fort in DL.  SoV came out and I moved to GD and killed giants, to get my drakel icegrinder.  I also spent some time in EJ, and TT.  I then soloed in SS and then to the Giant Fort in BW.  Most of the above zones are alot like EF with plenty of wondering mobs.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
